1
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:53,680
I'm just offering you a good option,
a life where you don't have to struggle.

2
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:57,200
A house, a car, anything you want,

3
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:58,320
I can give it to you.

4
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:01,480
What kind of person is Mr. Kritsana?

5
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:03,440
Has he done something to you?

6
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:07,440
With evidence this clear,

7
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:08,400
how can you deny it?

8
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:09,760
Oon, what's wrong?

9
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:12,640
I can't build a future for you anymore.

10
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,760
I've been suspended from work.

11
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:15,120
What happened?
Did someone do something to Aioon?

12
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:19,080
I don't know.
I just know it's about her work.

13
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:28,040
- Oon?
- FIFA, it's me, Fun. Can you talk?

14
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,800
Oh, yeah.

15
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:32,240
What happened? Can you tell me everything?

16
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:36,920
Some documents were sent to the company.

17
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:41,400
Then Nu said that
Oon and I were involved in fraud.

18
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,200
That's basically what happened.

19
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:57,080
Then let's meet tomorrow at my place.

20
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,200
What time works for you?

21
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,160
Around 9 a.m.

22
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,400
Okay, see you then.

23
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,896
I don't believe it.
Aioon would never do something like that.

24
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:11,440
I don't believe it either.
Someone has to be behind this.

25
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:37,080
For now, you should get some rest.

26
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,960
We'll figure it out tomorrow.

27
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,800
Trust me.

28
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:16,200
Can you think of anything else?

29
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:24,520
This project was strange.
It got approved really fast.

30
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:28,560
They requested me to be the designer
when we had never worked together before.

31
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:32,480
Honestly,
I'm not that well-known in the industry.

32
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:35,800
Exactly. If they wanted reputation,

33
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:39,240
wouldn't Nu have been a better choice?
He's a certified professional engineer.

34
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,320
True.

35
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,600
Oh, and the other day, Mr. Kritsana

36
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,880
was the one who called me to add
that paint company to the vendor list.

37
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:54,000
Then Mr. Kritsana

38
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:56,200
is definitely suspicious.

39
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,160
FIFA, call him.

40
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:05,320
Wait. Don't forget to record the call.

41
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:09,040
MR. KRITSANA CONSULT

42
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,040
RECORDING WILL BEGIN
AFTER THE CALL IS CONNECTED.

43
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,760
Hello, Mr. Krit. Can you talk?

44
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,840
What is it, Mr. Thanwa?

45
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:25,320
Well, about

46
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,880
the paint company
you asked me to add to the vendor list.

47
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,400
What paint company?

48
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:36,040
The one you urgently called me about,

49
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,600
saying you'd send the memo later.

50
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:42,040
You must be mistaken. I never said that.

51
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,280
But

52
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,680
I don't have time for nonsense like this.

53
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:52,120
Hey? What the heck? Oon.

54
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,720
You were there that day.

55
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,240
Yeah, what the heck?

56
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,480
Oh, and there's more.

57
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:07,400
The quotation was overpriced,

58
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:10,800
and there were payments
from contractors too. I took photos.

59
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,120
Here.

60
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,680
Oh, that machine?
The one you asked me to check?

61
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,720
Yeah. It's twice the normal price.

62
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:26,720
That's seriously messed up.

63
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:31,280
If he's denying it this shamelessly,
the only way is to get evidence from here.

64
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,200
Then I'll call them.

65
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,280
Hello, Accounting Department.

66
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,400
Hello,

67
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:55,280
I'd like to ask about a transfer
into Wirinya Sripitichote's account.

68
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,440
May I ask who's calling?

69
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,120
Wirinya.

70
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,440
Oh?

71
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:05,160
- Oon, don't bother calling anymore.
- Yeah, just go there.

72
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,760
There are no other choices.

73
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,600
- Let's go.
- Go.

74
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,760
Nueng, you stay here.

75
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,840
Yes. You're pregnant.

76
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,960
FIFA, come with me. Let's go.

77
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,640
Are you okay?

78
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:28,400
Yeah, go.

79
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,736
- Don't worry about me.
- You sure?

80
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,560
Yes. Just go.

81
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:32,680
Go.

82
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,640
Go. Don't worry about me. I can stay.

83
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,960
Okay.

84
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:05,440
- Hello.
- Hello.

85
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:08,960
I'd like to meet the head of accounting.

86
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,640
May I know your name?

87
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,200
Wirinya.

88
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,000
One moment, please.

89
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:20,640
Ms. Wirinya would like to meet you.

90
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,040
Yes. Yes.

91
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:28,920
Please wait over here.

92
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,960
This way, please.

93
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,800
If you don't arrange for them to meet us,

94
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,000
we will proceed with legal action.

95
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:26,160
We will pursue this case to the end
without the possibility of a settlement.

96
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:28,240
You have five minutes.

97
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,160
Hello.

98
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:54,240
The person who set the specifications
will explain everything.

99
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:12,320
I want to know

100
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:16,280
why your company
transferred money into my account.

101
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:19,680
You're part of Mr. Kritsana's team, right?

102
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:22,720
What do you mean by Mr. Kritsana's team?

103
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,560
Yeah, what does that mean?

104
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,480
Look, let me explain.

105
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:38,200
I have a complex project. Interested in
getting your brand onto the vendor list?

106
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,000
I am.

107
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:43,760
But there's a processing fee.

108
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,800
Please go ahead and name your price.

109
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,040
Thirty thousand?

110
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,400
Deal?

111
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,560
I don't have much time.

112
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:21,200
- I'll take that as your decision.
- Mr. Krit.

113
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,800
Wait.

114
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:27,120
Fine. I agree.

115
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,920
I'll get your brand onto the vendor list.

116
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,520
I'll send you the account number.

117
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,160
That's evil.

118
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:44,480
Do you realize
I had nothing to do with this?

119
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,360
How are you going to take responsibility?

120
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,560
Maybe we should let the law handle this.

121
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:58,320
Mr. Wasan,

122
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:03,120
why don't you write a statement
and take your thirty thousand back?

123
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,480
Excuse me,

124
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:10,200
have you tried contacting Mr. Kritsana?

125
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,440
Yes.

126
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,080
He said he knows nothing.

127
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,000
Nothing?

128
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,400
How could he not know?

129
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,680
Exactly.

130
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:23,480
That's what he said.

131
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:29,400
Then I'll proceed with legal action
against your company

132
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:33,520
for defamation.

133
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,440
I'm not sure if this will help.

134
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:42,920
I have an audio recording

135
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,640
of Mr. Kritsana.

136
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,920
- Can we hear it?
- Yes.

137
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:54,160
Hello, is this Mr. Kritsana?

138
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,280
Yes.

139
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,920
The processing fee for the complex project

140
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:02,640
has to be transferred
to Ms. Wirinya Sripitichote's account.

141
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,840
30,000 baht. Is that all correct?

142
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,080
What's your problem?

143
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:11,520
I see that it's not your account,

144
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:14,520
so I wanted to confirm the details again.

145
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:20,080
If you're going to be this difficult,
I'll remove your brand.

146
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,160
Transfer it to where I told you.

147
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:30,120
If you don't want this to escalate

148
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:34,440
and you want to prove your innocence,
give us the recording.

149
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:36,720
Yes, of course.

150
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,320
Excuse me.

151
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:45,240
I don't know how this will end.

152
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:48,200
But let me give you a piece of advice.

153
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:52,440
You shouldn't have done this.

154
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,960
I've seen your intumescent paint.

155
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:58,200
Your product meets the standards.

156
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:02,400
You should present it honestly

157
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:06,480
instead of bribing your way
onto the vendor list.

158
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,400
Krit is too cunning.

159
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:27,080
Even if we have an audio clip,
he'll say it's AI.

160
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,720
We need video evidence.

161
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,280
Then what do we do?

162
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,960
- Let me be the bait.
- No.

163
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,440
I don't want you going alone.

164
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:44,680
Who said I'd go alone?

165
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:57,400
PAFUN

166
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:00,760
So you've figured out who to choose.

167
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,560
Yes, Fun?

168
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,320
Do you have time to talk to me?

169
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,240
Sure.

170
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,240
Well, I need some advice.

171
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,000
Can we meet?

172
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:20,960
What is it about?

173
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:24,000
About your old offer.

174
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,920
I wonder if you still remember it.

175
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:30,440
Of course. What time works for you?

176
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:37,080
Can we meet now? I'll send the location.

177
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:38,920
Sure.

178
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,640
See you.

179
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,280
I seriously want to rip his hair out.

180
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:49,640
In the end, you chose me.

181
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,880
I'm parked on the second floor,

182
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,520
Pillar N45.

183
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,080
You can park next to me.

184
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,400
Krit.

185
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,480
Nice car.

186
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,520
You want one?

187
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:27,240
I'm thinking about it.

188
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,120
Can I borrow your keys?

189
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:43,840
Once we're done tonight,
you can get your new car tomorrow.

190
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:21,200
What are you trying to do?

191
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,119
What about you?

192
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:28,880
- Hello, is this Mr. Kritsana?
- Yes.

193
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:31,600
The processing fee for the complex project

194
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:35,040
has to be transferred
to Ms. Wirinya Sripitichote's account…

195
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,360
You teamed up?

196
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:40,040
Did you do it?

197
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:45,160
Yeah. So what?

198
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:48,600
Who would believe you?
I'll just say it's AI.

199
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:52,880
Then what about this invoice?

200
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,360
AI too?

201
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,080
Yeah. So what?

202
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,640
And the bribe from contractors?

203
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,400
Park the car and come here.

204
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,680
Mr. Krit.

205
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,000
Here it is.

206
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,640
There's one more client left.

207
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:24,800
Which one?

208
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,320
Air duct.

209
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,400
You can go now.

210
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:43,320
Yeah, I did all of it.

211
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,360
But what can you do

212
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:49,840
with evidence like this?
Who'd be stupid enough to believe you?

213
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:54,280
Let me tell you something.

214
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,960
There are no CCTV cameras around here.

215
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:02,360
I'm a consultant,
while you're just engineers.

216
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,680
The owner will obviously believe me
more than you.

217
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:05,840
And besides,

218
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:09,560
the evidence clearly shows
the money went into your account.

219
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:16,880
You really have no dignity. Maybe you
should borrow Aunt Sa-Ngad's skirt.

220
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,960
You've got such a mouth.
Let me teach you a lesson.

221
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,200
- You!
- Go ahead.

222
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,080
Fun, please.

223
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,920
For the sake of our friendship.

224
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:52,080
I did all of this
because I wanted to marry you.

225
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,480
Delete that clip.

226
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:58,560
I'll fix Aioon's situation

227
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,280
and make it like
none of this ever happened.

228
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,240
Disgusting.

229
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:07,920
Before this, you said I didn't have
to leave Aioon just have fun with you.

230
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:11,400
And now you're saying
you want to marry me?

231
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:15,520
Fun, I'm sorry.

232
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,760
Tell me how much you want.

233
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,720
I'll give you anything. I have plenty.

234
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,920
I'll write you a check right now.

235
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:23,960
- Or cash?
- Let me give this to you.

236
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:30,440
We're not just filing a police report.
We'll inform the owner

237
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:32,040
and the company too.

238
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,840
And if you think no one will believe us,
go ahead and try.

239
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,600
Damn it!

240
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:50,600
Is it happening again?
Do you want me to sleep here with you?

241
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:54,600
It's okay. It'll get better.

242
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,800
If you can't handle it, call me.

243
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,680
Is Nubnueng asleep?

244
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:37,640
Yes.

245
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:54,120
Go shower.
I'll gather the evidence while I wait.

246
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:25,160
Fun…

247
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:39,960
If I

248
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:43,640
couldn't find the evidence
to prove my innocence…

249
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:48,200
If I couldn't be an engineer…

250
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:54,160
If I couldn't take care of our family…

251
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,240
And if I couldn't.

252
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:04,720
I would still love you.

253
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:07,560
That's a truth that won't change.

254
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:15,160
I don't know when I fell in love with you.

255
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:19,800
I just realized one day that I already had.

256
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,240
So,

257
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,720
whether you can do it or not,

258
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:32,280
you're still you,

259
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,160
the person I fell in love with.

260
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:58,440
Thank you for trusting me.

261
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,640
EVIDENCE

262
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:30,240
EVIDENCE

263
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:33,920
I've sent all the evidence
to your email, Nu.

264
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:39,840
Okay, I got it.
I'll forward it to HR right away.

265
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:41,760
I'll call you as soon as there's an update.

266
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:45,120
Okay. Thank you, Nu. Goodbye.

267
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:54,360
With evidence this clear,
Krit won't get away with it.

268
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:57,000
He can kiss his future goodbye.

269
00:25:57,640 --> 00:26:00,160
Such a shame. If I'd gone that day,

270
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:02,960
he would've met my foot too.

271
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:06,160
Pregnant lady, calm down.

272
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:12,000
Well, when's
your next doctor's appointment?

273
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:15,120
- This Friday.
- This Friday?

274
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,560
In just a few months,
we'll get to meet the little one.

275
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:26,280
So, what should the little one call me?

276
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:29,800
My mom is your older cousin,

277
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:31,480
so technically I'm your niece.

278
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:34,400
That means my baby
should call you Grandma. Grandma Oon.

279
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:37,680
Nueng, I'm not that old.

280
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:39,120
And you

281
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,560
- should be…
- Stop.

282
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,040
Don't say it.

283
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,560
Fine, I won't say it. Granny.

284
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:46,720
Nueng.

285
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,680
I'll wait until after you give birth.

286
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:56,960
I'll have the little one call me Mommy.

287
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,320
Mommy.

288
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:00,440
Then what about me?

289
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:04,680
If the little one calls you Mommy,
what should they call me?

290
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,960
Mommy too.

291
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:09,040
Mommy Fun. Mommy Oon.

292
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:20,160
Please have a seat.

293
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:28,360
I owe you an apology, Ms. Wirinya,
Mr. Thanwa, and to your company, Mr. Nu,

294
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,920
for all the damage this has caused.

295
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:34,520
It's alright.
I won't pursue anything against you.

296
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:38,720
We were all victims in this.

297
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:42,680
My lawyer has already filed
a police report against Mr. Kritsana.

298
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:46,000
The police have issued an arrest warrant
and are tracking him down.

299
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:49,400
I've spoken
to the detective handling the case.

300
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:53,400
They expect to bring him in
to face legal action very soon.

301
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,800
- Alright.
- Thank you.

302
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:09,920
Thank you, Nu, for helping us.

303
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:13,280
Well, Oon,

304
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:17,800
about your professional license test,
how's your portfolio?

305
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,480
It should be complete
by the end of this month.

306
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:22,800
- I'm rooting for you.
- Thank you.

307
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:25,200
Alright, back to work.

308
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:06,480
UPDATE THE COORDINATES
FOR THIS POINT AS WELL

309
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:14,800
PROFESSIONAL ENGINEER
LICENSE PROMOTION INTERVIEW.

310
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:55,240
- Here, warm milk.
- Thanks.

311
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:58,000
- What are you watching?
- This. I'm checking this out.

312
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:07,040
Oon-Oon, are you free tomorrow?

313
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:09,560
Tomorrow?

314
00:30:09,640 --> 00:30:13,760
No, I'm not. I have meetings
with Mr. Anan's team all day.

315
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,360
Why?

316
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:19,560
Nueng has her checkup tomorrow,

317
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,480
but no one's free to go with her.

318
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:24,920
I have to go receive a client brief on-site.

319
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:28,320
Hey, did you guys forget something?

320
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:31,000
I lived alone for years abroad.

321
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,880
Going to the hospital alone is easy.
No need.

322
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:38,960
Then how about this?
My meeting is at eleven.

323
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:41,720
I'll drop you off first,

324
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,800
but I might not be able
to stay until you're done.

325
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,400
Actually, you don't have to.
I can go alone.

326
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,560
Don't make me worry, okay?

327
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:55,640
Fine, fine. Do whatever you want.

328
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,480
If you want to go, then go.

329
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:58,880
Let me see that.

330
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,520
What is it?

331
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:09,560
So pretty.

332
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,200
Here.

333
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:30,200
Hey!

334
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:32,280
Nueng.

335
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:36,640
You spilled it.

336
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:40,800
Let me see.

337
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:57,400
Good job. Here, take a tissue.

338
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:01,440
Well, I have to go now.

339
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:04,360
Yeah, go ahead. I'll be fine alone.

340
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,720
- Are you sure?
- Sure.

341
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:08,160
- Okay.
- Don't worry.

342
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,800
- Bye.
- Bye. Good luck.

343
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,960
Ms. Kanyavee, please come in.

344
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:23,240
Okay.

345
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:41,080
Congratulations.

346
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:44,000
The baby's heart rate is normal.

347
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:47,280
The baby is healthy
and developing well for its age.

348
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:07,120
Nueng, please tell the driver

349
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:09,160
to wait for me.
I'm going to the district office.

350
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:11,520
Okay. Please wait a moment.

351
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:13,040
Are you going to make an ID card?

352
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,840
No, I'm going to make a will.

353
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:18,040
A will? At the district office?

354
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:20,880
These days, you can do it there too.

355
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:24,960
There have been some inheritance disputes
in my hometown,

356
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:27,240
so I want to settle everything.

357
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:30,200
I'll transfer everything to Pa.

358
00:33:30,280 --> 00:33:32,800
That's it. So, where did you go?

359
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:36,680
I went to the hospital.
I had an appointment.

360
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:38,560
Okay. I'll go now.

361
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:44,800
Aunt Wi, can I go with you?

362
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:48,000
I want to make a will too.
What documents do I need?

363
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:51,960
Just your ID card and house registration.

364
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,680
But I don't have my house registration.

365
00:33:57,320 --> 00:34:00,000
Everything can be done
at the district office now.

366
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,400
You can request a copy at the counter.

367
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:06,360
With me around, there's no need to worry.
I'm good at this. Okay?

368
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,440
Okay.

369
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:08,639
Get back in.

370
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:09,719
Okay.

371
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,600
Let's go.

372
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,560
FIFA.

373
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:26,560
What happened to your neck?

374
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:29,159
Slept wrong. It's stiff.

375
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:32,040
How do you even sleep like that?

376
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:34,679
Did you see a doctor?

377
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:38,080
Yeah. I took the morning off
and just got back.

378
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,760
- Good.
- Yeah.

379
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:43,560
Oh, yeah, I saw your girlfriend

380
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:46,280
and your relative at the hospital.
The pregnant one.

381
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:50,080
- Oh, Nubnueng.
- Yeah, that one.

382
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:52,199
I don't remember names well.

383
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:56,600
If I didn't know Pafun was your
girlfriend, I'd think they were a couple.

384
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:02,200
You're crazy.
Fun just likes taking care of people.

385
00:35:02,720 --> 00:35:04,720
And Nubnueng is my relative.

386
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:07,560
Yeah, yeah, just kidding.

387
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:11,000
You should go get your mouth treated too.

388
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:12,320
- Huh?
- Yeah,

389
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,920
sounds like a potty mouth.

390
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:18,320
Just kidding.

391
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:22,400
Yeah, I'm going back to work.
I was just kidding, yeah?

392
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:24,360
- Get well soon.
- Thanks.

393
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:41,280
Jay, can you recheck this for me?

394
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:55,320
Wow, what did you buy? That's a lot.

395
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,640
Come on, I'll help.

396
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:05,160
- Come, I already unwrapped the fish.
- What's the occasion?

397
00:36:05,240 --> 00:36:07,080
You'll see. Here, the plate.

398
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:11,200
- It should be bamboo soup.
- Smells so good.

399
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:15,480
That's a lot. I'm hungry already.

400
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,480
Pour it slowly. Be careful not to spill.

401
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:23,040
Hey, what's that box?

402
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:27,960
What?

403
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:35,520
What is it?

404
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:39,000
So, I already know if our baby

405
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:40,960
is a boy or a girl.

406
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:58,880
Does anyone want to guess first?

407
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:00,880
Me?

408
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:03,560
I think…

409
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:06,120
A boy.

410
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:07,640
A boy?

411
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:12,160
For me, either is fine.

412
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:17,440
Okay, let's reveal it.

413
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:20,120
- Ready?
- Ready.

414
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:22,680
- Calm down.
- One!

415
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,080
One, two, three!

416
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:39,320
A boy!

417
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:42,360
A boy! We got a boy!

418
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,400
A boy.

419
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:54,040
Look at this first. Let me show you.

420
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:55,240
Do you know what this is?

421
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:57,600
The ultrasound.

422
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:00,840
- The baby.
- At first, I thought if it's a girl,

423
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:03,200
I'd name her Nanfah,

424
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:06,680
but if it's a boy, I'd name him Phupha,

425
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:09,040
so he'd be strong like a mountain,

426
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,840
no matter the storm.

427
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:16,200
Phupha,

428
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:18,760
we'll meet you soon.

429
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,960
Come out and meet us soon, okay?

430
00:39:46,640 --> 00:39:49,840
I saw your girlfriend
and your relative at the hospital.

431
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:52,800
If I didn't know Pafun was your girlfriend,

432
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:54,880
I'd think they were a couple.

433
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:13,280
Oon.

434
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:14,880
I want to have a baby.

435
00:41:23,040 --> 00:41:24,520
Aren't you going to eat breakfast?

436
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,760
We already ate. Go ahead and eat.

437
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:19,880
I'm heading to work.

438
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:22,760
I'll check on her.

439
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:33,400
You barely ate.

440
00:42:34,600 --> 00:42:36,600
I'm late. I'll go now.

441
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:58,320
DAY OF PROFESSIONAL ENGINEER LICENSE
PROMOTION RESULT ANNOUNCEMENT.

442
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:13,680
I passed!

443
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:38,640
Hello.

444
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:45,600
That's funny.

445
00:43:58,480 --> 00:44:00,640
Watching in the dark like this
will ruin your eyesight.

446
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:05,840
Oon-oon.

447
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:09,200
Go.

448
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:28,560
Aren't you hungry?

449
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:32,400
No.

450
00:44:35,440 --> 00:44:37,000
When will you be?

451
00:44:38,720 --> 00:44:42,880
Whenever. I'll handle it myself.

452
00:44:44,040 --> 00:44:45,480
Go watch your movie.

453
00:44:52,800 --> 00:44:53,840
It hurts.

454
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:00,080
Are you jealous?

455
00:45:02,240 --> 00:45:04,040
No. Why would I be?

456
00:45:06,920 --> 00:45:08,800
Then why won't you look at me?

457
00:45:10,440 --> 00:45:13,160
If you don't talk, I'll get mad.

458
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:24,360
I don't know.

459
00:45:25,440 --> 00:45:27,600
I just don't like what I see.

460
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:32,000
Don't like what? Don't like me?

461
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:35,000
No.

462
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:40,440
I just don't like how I feel right now.

463
00:45:49,200 --> 00:45:50,600
Why are you smiling?

464
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:54,680
Because I know

465
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:57,120
you're like this

466
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:59,840
because you care about me.

467
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:08,160
Better?

468
00:46:15,360 --> 00:46:16,360
Better?

469
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:25,200
- Better?
- I'm better now.

470
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:35,000
Fun.

471
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:39,080
I passed the promotion exam.

472
00:46:39,840 --> 00:46:41,440
Really?

473
00:46:43,480 --> 00:46:45,200
Congrats!

474
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:47,160
You're amazing.

475
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:49,440
That means

476
00:46:50,440 --> 00:46:54,600
from now on, I'm ready.

477
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:58,160
If you want to quit your job
and start your own company,

478
00:46:58,240 --> 00:46:59,240
you can.

479
00:47:04,640 --> 00:47:06,280
Then you deserve a reward.

480
00:47:44,640 --> 00:47:46,920
Oon-oon, how much cash
do you have left right now?

481
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:48,160
Around 500 baht.

482
00:47:48,240 --> 00:47:51,280
Then make it last until the end
of the month. I'm not giving you more.

483
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:55,280
I think my water broke.

484
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:56,360
‪Your water broke?

485
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:58,640
‪Oon, The car keys aren't that way.

486
00:47:58,720 --> 00:47:59,720
‪Oh, right.

487
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:08,760
So this is what they mean
by beautiful pain.

488
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:14,000
Welcome to Mommies' family, Phupha.

489
00:48:36,960 --> 00:48:40,600
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
